cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC 

The paper discusses the design and implementation of a challenge for automated diagnosis of melanoma using dermoscopic images. This involves tasks such as lesion segmentation, feature detection, and disease classification, which are all related to computer vision (cs.CV). The challenge also involves research and development of algorithms, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of dermoscopic images could also relate to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the goal of the challenge is to support diagnosis of a lethal disease, which could involve human-computer interaction (cs.HC) in terms of designing interfaces for medical professionals to use the automated diagnosis tools.
